        "timestamp": "2022-05-13 14:08:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n> \n> https://logs.onap.org/onap-integration/gating//129135-4/k8s/k8s/kubernetes-status/pod-onap-cps-core-64ccd7896-klzzq-cps-core-logs.html\n\nCps chart is currently referring CPS version 3.0.1 (latest Jakarta)\nhttps://github.com/onap/oom/blob/master/kubernetes/cps/components/cps-core/values.yaml#L78\n\nThis 3.0.1 artifact does not have the Janino dependency that has been introduced more recently in CPS master branch for K. release. I presume this is the reason why the gating is failing.\n\nThen, I think that this OOM change would have to stay as WIP until CPS has a new release from master. When should we plan for such a release ? After OOM has created jakarta branch ? At K. release code freeze time ?",
